{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e319388b-117c-4038-8f0e-d95f170f97f0","content":"The working directory is empty, so I'll answer from .NET MAUI knowledge:\n\n**`ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"`** — ✅ This is correct for .NET 10. You need the namespace:\n```xml\nxmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n```\nThen apply `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` on your `ContentPage`. This adjusts padding so content avoids the notch/home indicator.\n\n**`IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"`** — ❌ This is **not** a valid .NET MAUI property. There is no `IgnoreSafeArea` on `Grid` or any layout. Your tutorial may be outdated or referencing a different framework.\n\n**To extend a background image behind the safe area**, the typical pattern is:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns:ios=\"...\"\n             ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\">\n    <Grid>\n        <!-- Background extends full screen -->\n        <Image Source=\"bg.png\" Aspect=\"AspectFill\" />\n        <!-- Content respects safe area via manual padding -->\n        <Grid Padding=\"{OnPlatform iOS='44,0,34,0'}\">\n            <!-- Your content here -->\n        </Grid>\n    </Grid>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nAlternatively, keep `UseSafeArea=\"True\"` on the page and place the background image in an `AbsoluteLayout` that fills the screen outside the safe padding.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5d2b6a35-d8bd-4eb5-bcfb-a3cbc7cbea66","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The working directory is empty, so there's no local codebase to search. Let me answer based on my knowledge about .NET MAUI safe area APIs.\n\nIn .NET MAUI (including .NET 10), the safe area handling for iOS works as follows:\n\n1. `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` - This is the correct iOS platform-specific approach. It's available via the `Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific` namespace. You add `xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"` and then use `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` on your ContentPage.\n\n\n2. `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` isn't a valid property in .NET MAUI—there's no such attribute on Grid or other layouts. The correct way to handle safe areas on iOS is through `Page.UseSafeArea`, which adjusts the page's padding to respect the safe area when enabled.\n\nIf you want content like a background image to extend behind the safe area (under the notch), you'd skip using `UseSafeArea` on the page and instead manage the layout manually to allow full-screen coverage.","outputTokens":980,"requestId":"4837:208367:A24AE4:BE1FC1:69F3FE17"},"id":"4f0667b8-67d4-4461-b59c-29f2a5a7eec8","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:13:12.309Z","parentId":"04ad3dbb-6d11-431d-bc68-bd79e6b51408"}
